title: Add test for visuals dimensionality reduction
body:
This PR adds tests for visuals dimensionality reduction i.e. it tests if UMAP and TSNE visualizations are created correctly for both 2D and 3D dimension.

There's also added support for `dashboard_name` parameter in order to prevent file overwrite when using two or more UMAP/TSNE visuals.

The result of the test looks as follows:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/72266394/230780993-c06bc8fd-a7c4-4286-b9bc-eddd144874e7.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/72266394/230781022-d0aa9c73-eab8-4ee8-9f5f-531a7b73f2d2.png)

However, there's a streamlit error when trying to view both of UMAP or both of TSNE on the dashboard (like in the test). This is because of the colliding `plot_name` key for streamlit checkbox that is internally set to `self.visual_type` (either "UMAP" or "t_SNE")  when two or more of the same type visuals are present. I believe the fix is slightly hard here since st_run.py has "UMAP" and "t_SNE" filenames hardcoded for plotting.

Let's brainstorm the easiest way to fix this.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/72266394/230781196-f5184ff0-90cc-4139-bbfc-322164eaa0e8.png)

title: Improvement of tests
body:
This PR is a work-in-progress for improvement of UpTrain tests.

- Current tests do not really test individual components extensively and are code from the example files.
- Smaller unit tests can be used to cover different scenarios, edge cases and error conditions.
- Tests should be more modular, readable and maintainable for future contributors, developers and users.
- Breaking down tests into smaller parts will help automate them via workflows and github actions if/when integrated.

Edit: Updates to tests will be spread across multiple PRs to make reviewing easier as discussed. For now, this PR contains the following changes:
- Documentation and explanation of Concept Drift Adwin test
- Change of Concept Drift DDM test to use synthetic data instead of code from the examples
- Addition of tests for `uptrain.core.classes.measurables.accuracy`

title: Example for LLM model
body:
As mentioned in #34, this example contains:
- An example to highlight how UpTrain can be used to smartly fine-tune a LLM
- A model signal using sentiment analysis
- A model signal using keyword search

This PR is opened as a draft because of the following TODOs (please add on others that are required):
- Improve code documentation
- Add uptrain logging to create plots showing loss and perplexity on Streamlit dashboard
- Add visualizations for things like weight of prediction of different words to provide a graphical representation of what the model thinks is the best masked word

Edit: I've added loss, perplexity and mask prediction score visualizations using the streamlit dashboard functionality.
